arch:property.oc:show_val: Medium sized unit comprising of bones mainly from sheep-size animals. The average fragment size is of a reasonable size 2-3 cm and the species identified are sheep/goat, cattle, possible equid and parts of the jaw of a young dog. Several human bones were also identified from this context. A few bones ca. 2-3% have been burnt to a range of temperatures, some digested bone is present. Overall the unit displays a low degree of integrity and would be typical of a midden deposit. Last number = 142
